Research assessing attitudes in Bosniaand Herzegovina suggests that men and women express similar levels of acceptance towards divorce (Study for Working Group on Gender statistics 2020: 30 – 31, Raw data – G, page 9). Similarly, the following results were reported by Raw data – I regarding the view on divorce in two cities in the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina:
• In Sarajevo, the majority believes that divorce is sometimes justified, and 1 maintains that it is never justified.
• In Banja Luka, the majority believesthat it is never justified.
Fact or fiction| Unpublished research report, by Patricia Kellogg & Zahid Shahbazi | 17 July
2020 |
In Tuzla, people are again divided in about half. One fifth believethat divorce is never justified, and that half of the people believes that it is only sometimes justified.
Education
Results show that the most educated persons are the most likely to disagree that divorce is always a mistake while the most educated persons are also the most likely to disagreethat divorce should be discouraged by any means necessary. Those who attended some years of university are the ones most likely to agree that the law should give equal treatment to both parties during divorce.
